By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan departed Abuja Monday morning on a condolence visit to Sokoto over the demise of Alhaji Hassan Danbaba who was head of Sokoto Caliphate kingmakers. Lawan is being accompanied on the trip by the Governor of Yobe State and Caretaker Chairman of the All Progressives Congress(APC), Mai Mala Buni. According to the statement signed by the Special Adviser (Media) to President of the Senate, Ola Awoniyi, others on the entourage include Senator Mohammed Sani Musa, Senator Ibrahim Danbaba, Sarkin Sudan Awwal Lawal, Sardauna Habib Fari and Alhaji Halilu Mohammed Modi. They are expected to proceed from the Sokoto airport straight to the Palace to commiserate with the Sultan of Sokoto and also offer prayers for the repose of the soul of the deceased. The Senate President and members of his delegation are due back in Abuja immediately after the visit. By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Senate President, Ahmad Lawan and the Yobe State Governor, Mai Mala Buni on Thursday morning departed Abuja for Kano to condole with the Emir of Kano, Aminu Ado Bayero, on the death of his mother, Hajiya Maryam Ado Bayero. This was disclosed… In "News" The President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan paid a visit to Kano on Saturday to attend the wedding Fatiha of daughters of one of his close associates, Alhaji Hassan Kafayos. The Senate President embarked on the trip from Abuja with the Governor of Yobe State and Chairman, Caretaker Extraordinary Convention… In "News" By Kingsley Okoye Abuja - The President of the Senate, Dr Ahmad Lawan, has swore in Sen. Ibrahim Danbaba as Senator representing Sokoto South in the National Assembly. Danbaba left the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the 8th Senate alongside Gov. Aminu Tambuwal, to join Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), where… In "News"